---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import Header from "../../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
import { site } from "../../data/site";
import "../../styles/legal.css";
---

<Base
  title={`Privacy Policy — ${site.fullName}`}
  description="Privacy policy for TRADER Gallery, Hamburg."
  lang="en"
  path="/datenschutz"
>
  <Header slot="header" lang="en" altPath="/datenschutz" />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap legal">
      <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

      <h2>1. Controller</h2>
      <p>
        The party responsible for data processing on this website is:<br />
        TRADER Gallery, represented by Vincent von Thien<br />
        {site.address.street}, {site.address.postal} {site.address.city}<br />
        Email: <a href={`mailto:${"gallery@trader-hamburg.example"}`}>gallery@trader-hamburg.example</a>
      </p>
      <p class="placeholder">
        <strong>Placeholder:</strong> add real contact details before publishing this site.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Hosting</h2>
      <p>
        This website is hosted by an external service provider. Personal data collected on this website is
        stored on the hosting provider's servers.
      </p>
      <p class="placeholder">
        <strong>Placeholder:</strong> add the hosting provider's name and address once the site goes live.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Collection and storage of personal data</h2>
      <p>
        When you access this website, our hosting provider automatically collects information in so-called
        server log files that your browser transmits automatically (e.g. browser type, operating system,
        referrer URL, date and time of access). This data cannot be attributed to a specific person and is
        evaluated solely to ensure trouble-free operation of the site and to improve our offering.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Cookies and tracking</h2>
      <p>
        This website currently does not use cookies or any tracking or analytics tools. Should this change,
        this privacy policy will be updated accordingly and, where required, your consent will be obtained in
        advance.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Contacting us</h2>
      <p>
        If you contact us by email, the information you provide is stored to process your inquiry and in case
        of follow-up questions. We do not pass this data on without your consent.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Your rights</h2>
      <p>You have the right at any time to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>request information about the personal data we process about you (Art. 15 GDPR),</li>
        <li>request correction of inaccurate data (Art. 16 GDPR),</li>
        <li>request deletion of your data stored with us (Art. 17 GDPR),</li>
        <li>request restriction of processing (Art. 18 GDPR),</li>
        <li>object to the processing of your data (Art. 21 GDPR), and</li>
        <li>request data portability (Art. 20 GDPR).</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        You also have the right to lodge a complaint with a data protection supervisory authority about our
        processing of your personal data. The competent authority is the
        <a href="https://datenschutz-hamburg.de/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
          Hamburg Commissioner for Data Protection and Freedom of Information
        </a>.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Changes to this privacy policy</h2>
      <p>
        We reserve the right to adapt this privacy policy so that it always complies with current legal
        requirements, or to implement changes to our services.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer slot="footer" lang="en" />
</Base>
